** Reminder of Your Responsibilities as an Airport ID Pass / Airside Driving Permit Holder  **<br>
<br>
Please thoroughly read through the attached tool box talk.<br>
Responsibility 4 of an ID pass holder states "Airport ID pass holders must be aware of ‘tail-gating’ at entry points into and around airside areas. Under no <br>
circumstances should access be allowed to someone else unless that person has been issued with a temporary ID pass and is under their escort"<br>
<br>
Ensure you are tapping your own ID on every maid-reader when entering and exiting secure areas, do not allow passengers or colleagues to "Tail-gait" through secure areas behind you.<br>
<br>
Any questions feel free to comment or contact the ML or DM.<br>
Please click on the confirmation button at the bottom of this post once you have acknowledged this.<br>
<br>
