ata-v-3a58b531="">PAUL RAMPTON</a><div class="newsfeed-post-sub-text" data-v-3a58b531="">Mar 31, 2023 12:48 PM · <span class="wa-link" data-v-55dda85c="" data-v-3a58b531="">Terminal 5, Terminal 4 and 35 more</span></div></div><div class="newsfeed-post-content" data-v-3a58b531="">**Flight Build Operations**<br>
<br>
Last week there was an incident in Terminal 3 baggage hall involving BA &amp; ABC.<br>
A full ULD was dropped onto the lateral roadway due to procedures not being followed by BA.<br>
ABC colleagues were working on the lateral under BA guidance and supervision, ABC colleagues were not at fault for this incident.<br>
This is a reminder for all staff that have received training by either BA, Cobalt or Dnata on this process:<br>
Please ensure you follow your training when working on these operations, training and instruction is provided for the safety of yourselves and your colleagues working around you.<br>
Always follow your training, never deviate from instructions, never try to take a short cut to make a process easier or quicker.<br>
Always follow and use green routes in all areas especially baggage.<br>
If you feel that a colleague from BA, Cobalt or Dnata are asking you to conduct an activity or process that is not safe then please inform the ML or DM straight away and await their instructions.<br>
Any questions or concerns please raise them to the ML or DM.<br>
<br>
Remember “Work Safe, Home Safe”<br>
<br>
Kind Regards,<br>
<br>
<br>
