ost-content" data-v-3a58b531="">*** ABC Drug and Alcohol Policy ***<br>
<br>
Good afternoon,<br>
<br>
Please see the attached ALS Drug and Alcohol Policy.<br>
<br>
Below are some segments from the policy, ensure you abide by this policy:<br>
*ABC enforce a zero alcohol tolerance for ALL employees and agency workers.<br>
*Employees and agency workers are not permitted to drink alcohol whilst on duty under any circumstances, this policy also applies to low alcohol or "alcohol free" drinks as staff should understand that the smell of drink on the breath can cause offence.<br>
*Staff must not consume alcohol before reporting for duty.<br>
*Employees who consume alcohol on duty (or who consume alcohol before reporting for duty) will be suspended for at least the duration of the period of duty and disciplinary action may be taken. If as a result of any further tests and at the disciplinary hearing the charge is proven, the member of staff concerned could be dismissed.<br>
<br>
Please read through the whole of this policy and abide by the principles of action adopted.<br>
