Ensure your PPE is fit for the weather and please remember to bring your bump caps every shift as we may be deployed into a contingency where bump caps are required as well as Winter wear.<br>
<br>
Drivers, please ensure that all tug checks are done correctly and signed off via IAuditor app on ML iPad. Also please make sure that you are wearing your seatbelts any time you tasked to drive. Always keep to the speed limits as BCO will do regular check with the speed gun in the baggage halls. Lastly if you are tasked to use an ABC/DHL Wessex please ensure you strap up the curtains before moving away. If you need to manoeuvre out of a difficult position, please inform the ML / TL on shift and we will be able to provide a banksman for you.<br>
<br>
